Description: Wooden quadruple kohl-tube inscribed with the name of Ahmose; and lid
Curator's comments: Possibly the same Ahmose as in EA 10102-4, 10107 (Glanville, JEA 14, 297). See also .10102-4 See also .10107 Published: Un Arte per la Belleza, Padua 1984, p. 52 [84] = Un Arte per la Belleza, Lugano 1984, p. 49 [103]. Egypt's Golden Age, Boston 1982, p.223 [280].
